<#tt0108330-wowlover_80667>
	schema:about <#tt0108330>;
	schema:author "wowlover_80667";
	schema:dateCreated "Mon Apr 06 2015 00:00:00 GMT+0200 (Mitteleuropäische Sommerzeit)";
	schema:reviewRating 5;
	schema:headline " Sad but true...I still love it...";
	schema:reviewBody "Leonardo DiCaprio shows off his bad boy side in this film playing the rebellious teen Tobias Wolff in the late 50's. Toby or Jack as he likes to be called smokes cigarettes curses strongly drinks liquor and hangs out with his naughty friends for fun. He was once that innocent boy who just wanted to find a father that would last longer than a month and searched for Uranium with his mother Caroline for money. Roy Caroline's new boyfriend is very naughty and just wants kisses from his baby. Caroline and Toby have had enough and drive away in the old Nash Ambassador. Caroline meets a man named Dwight Hanson who is abusive to Toby behind her back which only makes Toby worse. I love how they use the nice songs from the 50's like Summertime Blues by Eddie Cochran. It's a very nice story based on the book and like The Basketball Diaries it leaves outchanges a few things but otherwise it's one of Leo's best films. At the end he cries when his mother leaves to get a real job and Toby grows up to be a better boy. 910.".

