<#tt0108330-JJohns>
	schema:about <#tt0108330>;
	schema:author "JJohns";
	schema:dateCreated "Tue Feb 04 2003 00:00:00 GMT+0100 (Mitteleuropäische Normalzeit)";
	schema:reviewRating 8;
	schema:headline " This Boy's Life was disturbing";
	schema:reviewBody "A very good movie brought on by good actors but very disturbing to watch even again. I won't watch it again. I think what made this one a winner aside from the acting is in the story telling. It's based on a true story of the lead guy played by DeCaprio. I was impressed with him and especially in Gilbert Grape. I think for his age at the time he carried his role well to play a kid tormented by a truly disturbed and oh so abusive step father played far too well by DeNiro. I hope DeNiro doesn't share the qualities of his character in real life. He did a good job and that's what a good movie is all about. Movies that imitate real life along with good acting produces good reviews and ticket sales to me. But like I said I'm not dying to see it again.".

<#tt0108330-JJohns-random>
	rdf:type onyx:EmotionSet;
	onyx:emotionText "A very good movie brought on by good actors but very disturbing to watch even again. I won't watch it again. I think what made this one a winner aside from the acting is in the story telling. It's based on a true story of the lead guy played by DeCaprio. I was impressed with him and especially in Gilbert Grape. I think for his age at the time he carried his role well to play a kid tormented by a truly disturbed and oh so abusive step father played far too well by DeNiro. I hope DeNiro doesn't share the qualities of his character in real life. He did a good job and that's what a good movie is all about. Movies that imitate real life along with good acting produces good reviews and ticket sales to me. But like I said I'm not dying to see it again.";
