<#tt0119349-merylmatt>
	schema:about <#tt0119349>;
	schema:author "merylmatt";
	schema:dateCreated "Mon Jul 13 2009 00:00:00 GMT+0200 (Mitteleuropäische Sommerzeit)";
	schema:reviewRating 1;
	schema:headline " Incredibly Depressing and Boring";
	schema:reviewBody "Wow I thought American Beauty was a tough film to watch. This movie is extremely depressing. Bored suburban families in 1973 I do not see any redeeming qualities in any of the characters that make me want to sympathize with any of them. Mom's Joan Allen and Sigourney Weaver and their husbands played by Kevin Kline and Jamie Sheridan wander aimlessly around having affairs trying to connect with their kids and survive. Joan Allen playing a straight laced uptight character  what a stretch. Signourney is distant aloof Kevin Kline clueless and emasculated as always.There is nothing ground breaking here. Everyone is shown with all of the wrinkles flaws and foibles of everyday people. No heroes in this movie. Great movie if you want to see life as it is but why not just look out the window? It's all there everyday and this flick does nothing to shed light on our lives. Hey did you know that unsupervised teens will experiment with sex and drugs?".

